## **Step \#4: Prizes**   
Say it out loud: The point of a hackathon is not the prize. 

I‚Äôve been to nation-wide university hackathons with $500+ worth of prize. It was cool, sure, but 1\) not winning crushes other people‚Äôs spirit and 2\) it encourages competition instead of cooperation. 

We want a helpful, encouraging environment. Not a competitive, Banking-esque one. 

The prize for each person on the winning team should be less than $30 USD. 

Giving a prize for the top 3 is usually the deal, but this can change depending on your event (and budget). Also, most events have ‚Äúspecial categories‚Äù like Funniest or Best Design. These are organizer‚Äôs-pick, so that‚Äôll have more logistics (organizers will have to gather in a room and talk, etc).

